title: Comment on Jeb Bush – Unhappy Campaigner (Limerick) by Thomas Gorman
text:
« Yet Another Benghazi Hearing Limerick (2-Verse) Jeb Bush – Unhappy Campaigner (Limerick) 
Jeb Bush is sounding bummed these days about the toxic nature of the race to be the Republican presidential nominee: 
I’ve got a lot of really cool things I could do other than sit around, being miserable, listening to people demonize me and me feeling compelled to demonize them. That is a joke. Elect Trump if you want that. 
It seems Jebbie objects to the slings And arrows of primary swings; Having chosen to run, He just ain’t havin’ fun… And would rather do “really cool things.” 
Tags: Campaign Satire , Election Humor , Jeb Bush   Sunday, October 25th, 2015 at 12:41 am and is filed under Campaign Humor , Election Satire , GOP Humor , Jeb Bush   , White House .   “Jeb Bush – Unhappy Campaigner (Limerick)” Thomas Gorman
